Wash and dry all produce.

Drain @mango{4%ounce}. Finely dice @roma tomato{1}.

Halve and peel @red onion{1}; thinly slice one half. Mince a few slices until you have 1 TBSP.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Halve, core, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1} into strips.

> For 4 servings, thinly slice whole onion; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP. For 4, zest 1 lime and quarter both.

In a #small bowl{}, combine mango, tomato, minced onion, lime zest, and juice from half the lime. Season with @salt{pinch}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano, sliced onion, and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and lightly charred, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if veggies begin to brown too quickly.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, @blackening spice{1%tablespoon}, and a big pinch of salt. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces and stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1} and 2 TBSP water; bring to a simmer.

Return veggies to pan, stirring, until thoroughly combined.

> TIP: Add a splash or two of water, if necessary, until mixture is saucy.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{}. Microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with beef and veggie filling. Top with mango salsa and @smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon}. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.